The White House Office of the Vice President has released a statement on the new Recovery Act recipient reports that have been posted on Recovery.gov. These reports provide more detailed information on the use of Recovery Act funds during the first quarter of 2010. The Vice President highlights that these reports show that about 675,000 workers were funded last quarter, making it the largest quarterly direct job impact reported by recipients of Recovery Act funds. The statement emphasizes that these reports provide an unprecedented look at how Recovery Act dollars are being used in communities, and that the data will continue to be refined and improved. Overall, the Recovery Act is said to be on track to support 3.5 million jobs by the end of 2010.